<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-15089] CassandraNetworkAuthorizer::authorize should get role details from Roles, not directly from IRoleManager</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-15089</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If the network permissions cache doesn&apos;t contain any entry for a role, the authorize method is invoked on the configured INetworkAuthorizer. In the case of CassandraNetworkAuthorizer, this immediately checks whether the role in question has the LOGIN privilege set. It does this using the configured IRoleManager directly, which causes a read from the underlying table in system_auth. It should fetch the flag from Roles::canLogin, which uses the RolesCache, falling back to the IRoleManager if necessary.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
